 Queues of vehicles lined up for kilometres as motorists travelling to and from Hendrina were forced to pull off. Contract workers have aired their dissatisfaction since they have not received a cent yet for more than six months. Protesters have set alight some rubbish on the N11. Fulltime employees at Optimum Colliery as well as Woestalleen Colliery were denied access to their work place. Also read: Warning: N11 closed by protesters #TrafficUpdate Trucks carrying coal were pulled over by protesters and their loads were spilled onto the road to block passageway.
Several of these vehicles were also stopped in the middle of the road to create barriers. A coal truck’s trailer was tipped to spill coal onto the road. The protest scene is currently peaceful as members of the Police Force are manning the situation.  The entrance to Optimum is still blocked as police try to clear the scene.  Hawks members sent to jail for fraud WATCH: The Place of Refuge – Once a vibrant village, now a ghost town WATCH: Robbery caught on video, police looking for suspects Three counts of poaching in one week – and the toll keeps rising  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za